{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "bfad990b-571b-4fb1-a41a-c948981f0e1f",
    "name": "wger Workout Manager \u2013 QA Test Suite",
    "description": "Complete Postman collection for testing the wger REST API ([https://wger.de/api/v2/](https://wger.de/api/v2/)).\n\nwger is a free, open-source fitness & gym management platform used as a stand-in for Sportendo API testing practice. It shares the same architectural patterns: user registration/login, JWT auth, user-owned resources (routines = games), public read endpoints, admin/manager roles, and pagination.\n\n\ud83d\udcd6 API Docs: [https://wger.de/api/v2/schema/ui](https://wger.de/api/v2/schema/ui)  \n\ud83d\udcd6 Redoc: [https://wger.de/api/v2/schema/redoc](https://wger.de/api/v2/schema/redoc)\n\n\ud83d\ude80 QUICKSTART:\n\n1. Register free account at [https://wger.de/en/user/registration](https://wger.de/en/user/registration)\n    \n2. Set username + password in the Environment file\n    \n3. Run '\ud83d\udd10 TC-AUTH-01 Login' first \u2014 it auto-saves your Bearer token\n    \n4. All subsequent requests use that token automatically\n    \n\n\u26a0\ufe0f NOTE: wger rate-limits heavy usage. Space out Collection Runner executions.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "47933265",
    "_collection_link": "https://go.postman.co/collection/47933265-bfad990b-571b-4fb1-a41a-c948981f0e1f?source=collection_link"
  },
